From: Matthew Jackson <matthew@pq.io>
Subject: [PATCH 6/8] hw/display/apple-gfx-linux: add gpu_cores property

Expose a `gpu_cores=N` QEMU device property that caps the
number of Mesa lavapipe worker threads the paravirt GPU uses.
Default `0` means "unset; let lavapipe pick its own default
(host core count)"; `N > 0` maps to `LP_NUM_THREADS=N` via
`lagfx_device_descriptor_t::thread_count`, which the library
translates into the lavapipe environment variable before its
first Vulkan call.

Values above `LAGFX_GPU_CORES_MAX` (64) are clamped at
realize time with a `warn_report` - lavapipe's historical
`LP_MAX_THREADS` compile-time cap is 32, so 64 leaves
headroom for future lavapipe builds. Reset-only: lavapipe
reads the env var once at ICD init.

The property is defined on the PCI wrapper, not the common
state, so MMIO variants (if added later) can choose their
own default.

Signed-off-by: Matthew Jackson <matthew@pq.io>
